WEBVTT

00:01.349 --> 00:03.568
PREVIOUSLY ONWHITE COLLAR...

00:03.655 --> 00:05.396
Moz: I MOVED YOUR PORTION OF
THE TREASURE OUT OF THE COUNTRY.

00:05.483 --> 00:07.703
IT'S STILL WORTH MORE
THAN EITHER OF US

00:07.790 --> 00:08.965
COULD EVER SPEND
IN A LIFETIME.

00:09.052 --> 00:10.314
I DON'T WANT TO RUN
ANYMORE, MOZ.

00:10.401 --> 00:11.576
I'M --
AGENT KRAMER.

00:11.663 --> 00:13.448
HEAD OF THE BUREAU'S
D.C. ART CRIMES UNIT.

00:13.535 --> 00:15.580
SO YOU'RE THE ONE WHO TAUGHT
PETER EVERYTHING HE KNOWS.

00:15.667 --> 00:17.800
Peter: NEAL'S MY C.I.HE'S ALSO A FRIEND.

00:17.887 --> 00:20.150
"THE U.S. PROBATION OFFICE
IS CONVENING A HEARING

00:20.237 --> 00:23.240
TO DISCUSS THE COMMUTATION
OF YOUR SENTENCE."

00:23.327 --> 00:24.807
YOU COULD BE A FREE MAN.

00:24.894 --> 00:26.852
Woman: YOU'VE ALREADY SERVED TWO
YEARS OF A FOUR-YEAR SENTENCE

00:26.939 --> 00:28.419
WHILE CONFINED
TO A TRACKING ANKLET.

00:28.506 --> 00:30.073
I WON'T BE GOING ANYWHERE
ANYTIME SOON.

00:30.160 --> 00:31.770
THIS IS MY HOME NOW.

00:31.857 --> 00:33.163
Kramer: CAFFREY'S GOT A LOT
OF SECRETS.

00:33.250 --> 00:35.818
BUT IF I KEEP DIGGING,
WHO KNOWS WHAT WILL TURN UP?

00:35.905 --> 00:37.124
IF KRAMER DIGS UP
THESE THINGS --

00:37.211 --> 00:38.560
NEAL COULD GET
THE MAXIMUM.

00:38.647 --> 00:40.736
HE COULD GO BACK
TO PRISON.FOR A LONG, LONG TIME.

00:40.823 --> 00:42.216
YOU'RE COVERING FOR HIM.

00:42.303 --> 00:44.000
YOU BOX HIM IN,
HE'S GONNA RUN.

00:44.087 --> 00:46.046
THESE MARSHALS ARE HERE TO TAKE
NEAL CAFFREY INTO CUSTODY,

00:46.133 --> 00:49.223
AND HE'LL WORK FOR ME
IN D.C. PERMANENTLY.

00:49.310 --> 00:52.661
YOU UNDERSTAND THIS IS BEST
FOR EVERYONE, DON'T YOU?

00:52.748 --> 00:55.707
Peter: I DO KNOW
THAT HE HAS A GOOD HEART.[ ANKLET BEEPS ]

00:55.794 --> 00:57.405
Woman: DO YOU THINK
MR. CAFFREY IS REFORMED?

00:57.492 --> 00:59.537
AS LONG AS HE'S ON THAT ANKLET,
WE'LL NEVER KNOW.

00:59.624 --> 01:02.062
AS LONG AS WE TREAT HIM
LIKE A CRIMINAL,

01:02.149 --> 01:04.238
HE'LL ALWAYS THINK
THAT HE IS ONE.

01:04.325 --> 01:07.806
SHOULD NEAL CAFFREY'S SENTENCE
BE COMMUTED?

01:07.893 --> 01:09.678
YES.
NEAL SHOULD BE FREE.

01:25.520 --> 01:28.175
[ SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE ]

01:28.262 --> 01:32.831
Peter: I'M SAYING NEAL
SHOULD BE FREE.

01:32.918 --> 01:34.964
Neal:
I CAN TELL YOU ONE THING --

01:35.051 --> 01:37.401
I WON'T BE GOING ANYWHERE
ANYTIME SOON.

01:37.488 --> 01:39.273
Diana: PETER,
CAFFREY'S CUT HIS ANKLET.

01:39.360 --> 01:41.797
NEAL'S GONE.

01:41.884 --> 01:44.104
Peter: THAT PERSON YOU SAW
ON ROOSEVELT ISLAND --

01:44.191 --> 01:45.496
WHO WAS IT?

01:45.583 --> 01:49.065
Jones: E. PARKER,
WITNESS PROTECTION.

01:49.152 --> 01:52.721
Neal: WHEN THIS IS OVER,
I'LL TELL YOU EVERYTHING.

01:52.808 --> 01:55.245
Hughes: KRAMER THINKS YOU KNOW
MORE THAN YOU'RE SAYING.

02:00.424 --> 02:02.383
UNTIL THE DUST SETTLES,
KEEP YOUR HEAD DOWN,

02:02.470 --> 02:05.821
CLOSE SOME CASES,
AND FORGET ABOUT NEAL CAFFREY.

02:05.908 --> 02:07.518
[ WATER POURING ]

02:07.605 --> 02:09.694
Jones: PETER.

02:09.781 --> 02:11.218
PETER.

02:11.305 --> 02:12.741
JONES.
HEY.

02:12.828 --> 02:15.091
WHAT'D YOU BRING ME?WORK-UP
ON ANOTHER MAIL FRAUD.

02:15.178 --> 02:16.179
FOREIGN LOTTERY?

02:16.266 --> 02:18.138
MAGAZINE SWEEPSTAKES.

02:18.225 --> 02:20.879
OH, VARIETY --
SPICE OF LIFE.

02:20.966 --> 02:23.404
Collins:
IS THIS WHERE CAFFREY SAT?

02:23.491 --> 02:25.841
WHO'S THAT
AT NEAL'S DESK?

02:25.928 --> 02:28.060
NO IDEA.

02:30.759 --> 02:33.501
WELL, IT LOOKS LIKE
HE KNOWS YOU.

02:42.814 --> 02:45.339
HE'S GOT QUITE THE SWAGGER,
DOESN'T HE?

02:45.426 --> 02:46.818
YOU DIDN'T BLINK FIRST,
DID YOU?

02:46.905 --> 02:49.647
NO, I DIDN'T.
OH.

02:49.734 --> 02:51.606
I'VE BEEN INVITED
TO THE PARTY.

02:54.217 --> 02:56.785
Hughes: PETER,
THIS IS AGENT KYLE COLLINS.

02:56.872 --> 02:59.875
HE'S WITH O.I.A.

02:59.962 --> 03:01.398
WHAT BRINGS THE OFFICE
OF INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS

03:01.485 --> 03:03.400
TO WHITE COLLAR?NEAL CAFFREY.

03:03.487 --> 03:05.750
IT'S BEEN SIX WEEKS,

03:05.837 --> 03:07.970
AND THE BUREAU
HASN'T TURNED UP ONE LEAD

03:08.057 --> 03:10.277
ON ITS POSTER BOY FOR REFORM,

03:10.364 --> 03:12.279
WHICH IS WHY CAFFREY
NEEDS TO BE CAPTURED

03:12.366 --> 03:14.977
AND LOCKED AWAY FOR A LONG,
LONG TIME.

03:15.064 --> 03:16.718
AS YOU'RE AWARE,
WE'VE GOT AGENTS

03:16.805 --> 03:19.024
FLIPPING OVER EVERY MATTRESS
CAFFREY'S EVER SLEPT ON.

03:19.111 --> 03:21.853
BUT THOSE OTHER AGENTS
AREN'T PETER BURKE.

03:21.940 --> 03:24.029
[ CHUCKLES ]
I'VE GIVEN MY STATEMENTS.

03:24.116 --> 03:26.336
EVERYTHING I KNOW ABOUT NEAL
IS IN THE FILE.

03:26.423 --> 03:28.208
EVERYTHING THAT'S OFFICIAL,
MAYBE.

03:28.295 --> 03:29.992
BUT AGENT KRAMER
SEEMS TO THINK

03:30.079 --> 03:31.950
THAT YOU MAY HAVE LEFT OUT
THE GOOD STUFF.

03:32.037 --> 03:33.604
KRAMER SENT YOU.

03:33.691 --> 03:35.693
YOU KNOW, HE SHED
QUITE A BIT OF LIGHT

03:35.780 --> 03:38.392
ON YOUR RELATIONSHIP
WITH CAFFREY.

03:38.479 --> 03:41.612
AGENT COLLINS, IF BURKE SAYS
IT'S ALL THERE, IT'S ALL THERE.

03:41.699 --> 03:46.922
"NEAL CAFFREY
HAS 27 KNOWN ALIASES,

03:47.009 --> 03:48.706
"SPEAKS EIGHT LANGUAGES,

03:48.793 --> 03:50.404
"INCLUDING
CONVERSATIONAL SWAHILI.

03:50.491 --> 03:51.405
HE'D AVOID COUNTRIES
WITH EXTRADITION."

03:51.492 --> 03:52.797
THAT'S HELPFUL.

03:52.884 --> 03:54.451
"HE HAS A WEAKNESS
FOR BEAUTIFUL WOMEN AND..."

03:54.538 --> 03:57.237
[ CHUCKLES ]
I LOVE THISBIT OF INSIGHT.

03:57.324 --> 03:58.412
"HE RUNS."

03:58.499 --> 04:01.632
HMM. YES, HE DOES.

04:01.719 --> 04:03.939
ARE WE DONE HERE?NO.

04:04.026 --> 04:07.899
AGENT BURKE,
I'M GONNAFIND NEAL CAFFREY.

04:07.986 --> 04:11.599
AND YOU'RE GONNA
HELP ME DO IT.

04:14.123 --> 04:15.037
[ UP-TEMPO LATIN MUSIC PLAYS ]

04:49.245 --> 04:51.334
BUENOS DíAS, RODRIGO.

04:51.421 --> 04:53.467
[ LAUGHS ]
SEÑOR MAINE!

04:53.554 --> 04:54.729
¿ESTá LISTO?

04:54.816 --> 04:57.384
Sí, SEÑOR MAINE.
ESTá LISTO.

04:59.386 --> 05:00.952
WOW.

05:03.912 --> 05:06.784
[ SPEAKS SPANISH ]

05:06.871 --> 05:09.134
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:15.967 --> 05:17.142
[ BELL RINGS ]

05:17.229 --> 05:18.796
[ HORNS BLARE ]

05:23.888 --> 05:25.977
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

05:26.064 --> 05:28.023
THANK YOU.

05:28.110 --> 05:30.025
HERE YOU GO.

05:30.112 --> 05:31.243
Woman:
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

05:31.331 --> 05:32.332
THANK YOU.

05:37.075 --> 05:38.555
[ LAUGHS ]

05:43.691 --> 05:46.650
HEY, YOU DIDN'T
PAY FOR THAT!

05:50.741 --> 05:52.134
HERE.

05:54.223 --> 05:56.312
FOR HIS PAPAYAS,
HECTOR.

05:56.399 --> 05:57.444
OH, THANK YOU,
SEÑOR.

05:57.531 --> 05:58.706
SEE YOU IN A LITTLE BIT,
BUDDY.

05:58.793 --> 06:00.316
OKAY.

06:00.403 --> 06:02.927
[ GUITAR PLAYING ]

06:06.322 --> 06:10.370
PARDONAME, UH,
USTED CONOCE "MI VALERO"?

06:10.457 --> 06:11.849
Sí.

06:13.721 --> 06:15.853
SIGUEME.

06:15.940 --> 06:18.290
[ "MI VALERO" PLAYING ]

06:29.432 --> 06:30.738
BUENOS DíAS, MAYA.

06:30.825 --> 06:34.306
OH. HELLO, AGAIN,
NEW YORK.

06:34.394 --> 06:35.873
"MI VALERO."

06:35.960 --> 06:38.441
THAT'S THE LAST TIME I TELL YOU
ONE OF MY FAVORITES.

06:38.528 --> 06:40.617
THAT ALMOST
SOUNDS LIKE REGRET --

06:40.704 --> 06:43.272
SOMETHING YOU SAID
YOU DIDN'T BELIEVE IN.

06:43.359 --> 06:45.883
AFTER A FEW CAIPIRINHAS,
I SAY A LOT OF THINGS.

06:45.970 --> 06:47.842
Moz: HA!

06:47.929 --> 06:49.800
OH, YOUR USUAL TABLE
HAS EARS.

06:49.887 --> 06:52.847
OH, BARRY?
HE'S HARMLESS.

06:52.934 --> 06:54.762
HE WANTS TO UNIONIZE
MY SERVERS.

06:54.849 --> 06:56.328
VIVA HEALTH CARE!

06:56.416 --> 06:57.895
MORE OR LESS HARMLESS.

06:59.636 --> 07:01.246
SAY YES
TO DINNER TONIGHT.

07:01.333 --> 07:04.511
I'M SORRY.
I HAVE TO WORK.

07:04.598 --> 07:06.556
YOU'RE THE PROPRIETOR.

07:06.643 --> 07:09.429
I LIKE YOU, JAMES.
I DO.

07:09.516 --> 07:11.431
BUT MEN LIKE YOU
ARE TROUBLE.

07:11.518 --> 07:12.910
MEN LIKE ME?

07:12.997 --> 07:14.869
MEN WHO COME HERE
TO ESCAPE THEIR PAST.

07:14.956 --> 07:16.914
OH.

07:17.001 --> 07:18.525
I THINK
YOU'RE CONFUSING ME

07:18.612 --> 07:20.701
WITH THE GUY
WHO STEALS HECTOR'S PAPAYAS.

07:20.788 --> 07:23.704
[ CHUCKLES ]
AND IF YOU ARE,
I'M OFFENDED.

07:23.791 --> 07:25.314
ESTOY TAMBIEN.

07:25.401 --> 07:29.274
SO YOU'RE AN HONEST MAN
WHO HAS NOTHING TO HIDE.

07:29.361 --> 07:31.494
OPEN BOOK.

07:31.581 --> 07:34.062
YOU'RE FROM NEW YORK.
THAT'S ALL YOU'VE TOLD ME.

07:34.149 --> 07:35.759
IT'S THE BEST CITY
IN THE WORLD.

07:35.846 --> 07:38.196
THEN WHY'D YOU LEAVE?TO LIVE HERE.

07:38.283 --> 07:40.851
IN PARADISE.I'M SORRY, NEW YORK.

07:40.938 --> 07:43.027
YOUR OPEN BOOK
IS A WORK OF FICTION.

07:43.114 --> 07:44.594
MAYA, COME ON.

07:44.681 --> 07:47.858
ONE MOMENT OF HONESTY.
THAT'S ALL I'M ASKING.

07:47.945 --> 07:49.817
MAYBE THEN
I'LL CONSIDER DINNER.

07:58.129 --> 08:00.305
[ SIGHS ]

08:00.392 --> 08:04.266
IF IT ISN'T BARRY SOETORO --
CAREFREE TREASURE HUNTER.

08:04.353 --> 08:07.138
JUST SO I'M CLEAR,
YOU CAN HAVE ANY WOMAN YOU WANT,

08:07.225 --> 08:08.836
AND THE ONE WOMAN
YOU CHOOSE

08:08.923 --> 08:12.448
IS THE ONLY WOMAN
IN THE ENTIRE ARCHIPELAGO

08:12.535 --> 08:13.536
WHO DOESN'T WANT YOU.

08:13.623 --> 08:15.320
YOU HAVE YOUR PURSUITS,
I HAVE MINE.

08:15.407 --> 08:18.367
WELL, SHE HAS NO REASON TO
ASSUME WE'RE HIDING ANYTHING.

08:18.454 --> 08:20.848
EXCEPT THE FACT THAT THIS ISLAND
HAS NO U.S. EXTRADITION TREATY

08:20.935 --> 08:22.414
AND WE SHOWED UP
WITH LIMITLESS WEALTH.

08:22.502 --> 08:24.416
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:26.854 --> 08:28.551
YOU MISS IT?

08:28.638 --> 08:30.901
OF COURSE.

08:30.988 --> 08:32.424
BUT WHAT'S REGRET
GONNA GET ME?

08:32.512 --> 08:34.252
NOTHING.

08:34.339 --> 08:38.039
AND YOU'RE JAMES MAINE --
RICH, CAREFREE ISLAND RESIDENT.

08:38.126 --> 08:39.736
NEAL CAFFREY,
ON THE OTHER HAND, IS --

08:39.823 --> 08:41.695
IS A WANTED FUGITIVE.

08:41.782 --> 08:44.959
TOO BAD THE FBI
WON'T FORGET THAT.

09:03.064 --> 09:06.589
YOU THINK HE'S IN MILOS?
SPARTA, MAYBE?

09:06.676 --> 09:09.070
YOU KNOW,
THERE'S NOTHING IN HIS FILE

09:09.157 --> 09:11.376
ABOUT AN AFFINITY
FOR GREEK PHILOSOPHY.

09:11.463 --> 09:14.031
'CAUSE YOU'RE NOT GONNA
FIND NEAL STUDYING TRINKETS.

09:14.118 --> 09:15.990
AND WHY IS THAT?

09:16.077 --> 09:19.428
HE DISAPPEARS
THROUGH RE-INVENTION.

09:19.515 --> 09:21.517
THE MAN YOU'RE LOOKING FOR ISN'T
THE ONE WHO SAT AT THAT DESK.

09:21.604 --> 09:22.562
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:22.649 --> 09:24.215
THE DAY CAFFREY FLED,

09:24.302 --> 09:28.002
YOU SAID YOU FOLLOWED HIM
TO ROOSEVELT ISLAND.

09:28.089 --> 09:30.004
MM-HMM.

09:30.091 --> 09:31.832
YOU CLAIMED YOU DIDN'T
KNOW WHY HE WAS THERE
OR WHO HE MET WITH,

09:31.919 --> 09:34.095
AND YET YOU HAD
AGENT CLINTON JONES

09:34.182 --> 09:36.663
FLAG THE NAME E. PARKER,

09:36.750 --> 09:38.578
BUT YOU FAILED TO MENTION
THE PART ABOUT E. PARKER

09:38.665 --> 09:40.057
IN ANY OF YOUR OFFICIAL
STATEMENTS.

09:40.144 --> 09:41.755
WE COULDN'T CONFIRM
THE DETAILS.

09:41.842 --> 09:43.757
YOU TRIED TO GO
THROUGH WITSEC?
NO HELP.

09:43.844 --> 09:45.367
I'LL LET YOU KNOW
IF THAT'S TRUE.

09:46.890 --> 09:48.283
DID YOU LEAVE OUT
ANYTHING ELSE?

09:50.024 --> 09:53.288
HE LIKES TANDUAY RUM.

09:53.375 --> 09:56.160
NOPE. I'VE GOT PEOPLE ON
THE GROUND IN THE PHILIPPINES.

09:56.247 --> 09:57.771
HMM.

09:57.858 --> 10:00.687
THEN CLEARLY YOU KNOW MORE
THAN I DO.

10:03.254 --> 10:05.430
Elizabeth:
AW, THAT'S A SHAME.

10:05.517 --> 10:08.303
I LIKED PICTURING NEAL AND MOZ
TOURING THE COCONUT PALACE.

10:08.390 --> 10:10.044
WELL,
IF COLLINS HAS HIS WAY,

10:10.131 --> 10:11.698
YOU CAN START PICTURING NEAL
IN SING SING.

10:11.785 --> 10:12.873
THAT'S IF HE'S LUCKY.

10:12.960 --> 10:14.309
YOU WANT ME
TO KICK COLLINS' ASS?

10:14.396 --> 10:16.920
HMM. SIX WEEKS.

10:17.007 --> 10:18.618
SIX WEEKS
OF CHASING DOWN LEADS.

10:18.705 --> 10:20.097
EL,
HE'S MY RESPONSIBILITY.

10:20.184 --> 10:22.404
IF ANYTHING
WERE TO HAPPEN TO HIM...

10:22.491 --> 10:23.971
HONEY, KRAMER BACKED YOU
INTO A CORNER.

10:24.058 --> 10:25.668
YOU HAD TO LET NEAL GO.
YOU KNOW THAT.

10:25.755 --> 10:29.454
YEAH, AND NOW I KNOW THAT
COLLINS HAS ACCESS TO WITSEC.

10:29.541 --> 10:30.978
HE'S GOT A LEG UP.

10:31.065 --> 10:32.849
YOU STILL THINK THIS E. PARKER
KNOWS WHERE NEAL WENT?

10:32.936 --> 10:36.287
MY GUT'S TELLING ME THAT PARKER
IS THE KEY TO ALL OF THIS.

10:36.374 --> 10:37.898
AND YOU DON'T THINK
YOU CAN GET TO PARKER FIRST?

10:37.985 --> 10:40.117
NO.

10:40.204 --> 10:43.730
YOU KNOW, BUT MAYBE I COULD
COME IN A CLOSE SECOND.

10:43.817 --> 10:45.732
BY FOLLOWING COLLINS.

10:45.819 --> 10:48.952
YEAH, IF PARKER KNOWS
WHERE NEAL IS,

10:49.039 --> 10:51.651
MAYBE I CAN WARN HIM
THAT COLLINS IS COMING.

10:51.738 --> 10:53.914
WELL,
THAT'S A BIG "IF."

10:54.001 --> 10:56.177
YEAH. RIGHT NOW
THAT'S ALL I HAVE.

10:56.264 --> 10:57.874
AND IF ALL ELSE FAILS,

10:57.961 --> 11:01.791
YOU CAN
KICK COLLINS' ASS.

11:01.878 --> 11:03.488
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:03.575 --> 11:05.577
[ LATIN MUSIC PLAYS ]

11:12.715 --> 11:16.153
YOU KNOW, MOST NORMAL PEOPLE
MAKE SAND CASTLES OUT OF SAND.

11:16.240 --> 11:19.026
WHEN HAVE YOU EVER CONSIDERED US
NORMAL PEOPLE, MOZ?

11:19.113 --> 11:20.505
[ LAUGHS ]
YOUR POINT?

11:20.592 --> 11:22.551
LANGUAGE IS FLUID.

11:22.638 --> 11:26.163
OH.
SO IS YOUR LINEN SHIRT.

11:26.250 --> 11:27.948
ALL RIGHT. YOU MIND HANGING OUT
WHILE I CHANGE?

11:28.035 --> 11:29.863
OR I COULD GO MEET DOBBS
BY MYSELF,

11:29.950 --> 11:31.299
SAVE YOU THE TROUBLE.

11:31.386 --> 11:33.780
WE'RE PAYING THE GUY 25 GRAND
A MONTH FOR SAFE HAVEN.

11:33.867 --> 11:35.564
I THINK THAT'S EARNED ME
SOME FACE TIME.

11:35.651 --> 11:36.957
AS YOU KNOW,

11:37.044 --> 11:39.220
I VETTED A LOT OF LOCATIONS
FOR OUR FINAL REFUGE,

11:39.307 --> 11:41.265
AND WITH
OUR VERY SPECIFIC DEMANDS

11:41.352 --> 11:43.920
FOR LIFESTYLE AND SECURITY,
IT'S A SHORT LIST.

11:44.007 --> 11:46.662
BIG ENOUGH TO BLEND IN,
SMALL ENOUGH TO LIMIT EXPOSURE.

11:46.749 --> 11:47.924
I KNOW, MOZ.

11:48.011 --> 11:50.144
IF WE CROSS DOBBS
IN ANY WAY,

11:50.231 --> 11:52.755
OUR ONLY OTHER OPTION
IS ISLA PARADISO.

11:52.842 --> 11:54.322
SOUNDS NICE.

11:54.409 --> 11:56.106
IT'S A LEPER COLONY!

11:56.193 --> 11:58.152
AND CONTRARY
TO POPULAR OPINION,

11:58.239 --> 12:00.241
I DO NOT HAVE
THE COMPASSION OF JESUS.

12:00.328 --> 12:01.590
I'LL BE A SAINT.

12:01.677 --> 12:03.374
OH,
I GOT THIS FOR DOBBS.

12:03.461 --> 12:04.767
AND THIS WOULD BE?

12:04.854 --> 12:06.813
OH, A GOOD FIRST
IMPRESSION.

12:09.467 --> 12:12.601
IT LOOKS LIKE DOBBS
IS DOING OKAY FOR HIMSELF.

12:12.688 --> 12:15.735
[ CHUCKLES ]
HE'S GOT THE WHOLE ISLAND WIRED.

12:15.822 --> 12:17.998
CLEARLY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:25.614 --> 12:28.312
SHE'S BEAUTIFUL.

12:28.399 --> 12:31.011
THIS ONE TOOK ME
ALMOST A YEAR.

12:31.098 --> 12:32.621
HALF THE CHALLENGE
IS FINDING MATERIALS

12:32.708 --> 12:33.840
THIS FAR
FROM THE MAINLAND.

12:33.927 --> 12:36.233
MR. DOBBS,
I'D LIKE TO INTRODUCE YOU

12:36.320 --> 12:37.887
TO MY ASSOCIATE,
JAMES MAINE.

12:37.974 --> 12:39.715
MR. MAINE.

12:39.802 --> 12:41.499
THE NAMES WE CHOOSE
CAN BE VERY TELLING.

12:41.586 --> 12:42.762
WHERE DOES YOURS
COME FROM?

12:42.849 --> 12:44.241
THE U.S.S. MAINE.

12:44.328 --> 12:46.940
DIDN'T THE MAINESHIPWRECK
IN ROUGH SEAS?

12:47.027 --> 12:48.506
[ CHUCKLES ]
SUFFICE IT TO SAY,

12:48.593 --> 12:49.986
IT WASN'T
A PLANNED RETIREMENT.

12:50.073 --> 12:51.466
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:51.553 --> 12:53.990
THOUGHT YOU MIGHT APPRECIATE
A NEW CANVAS.

12:54.077 --> 12:55.687
LOOK AT THIS.

12:55.775 --> 12:59.169
DIMPLE WHISKEY.
1935.

12:59.256 --> 13:01.911
NOT EASY TO COME BY IN
THESE PARTS. HOW'D YOU FIND IT?

13:01.998 --> 13:03.347
WELL, HOW WE EMPTIED IT
IS THE BETTER STORY.

13:03.434 --> 13:04.392
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:04.479 --> 13:05.915
I'M SURE IT IS.

13:06.002 --> 13:09.353
I ASSUME YOU HAVE
SOMETHING ELSE FOR ME?

13:09.440 --> 13:13.575
WOW.
BUILT ALL THESE YOURSELF?

13:13.662 --> 13:16.534
I'VE BEEN ON THIS ISLAND
ALMOST 20 YEARS.

13:16.621 --> 13:19.624
IT'S IMPORTANT
TO HAVE HOBBIES.

13:19.711 --> 13:20.930
WELL, I HAVE TO ADMIT,

13:21.017 --> 13:22.366
I DON'T KNOW MUCH
ABOUT SHIPS IN BOTTLES.

13:22.453 --> 13:25.021
WELL,
PLANNING IS CRITICAL.

13:25.108 --> 13:27.589
WHEN ALL THE PIECES ARE SET,

13:27.676 --> 13:30.984
IT ONLY TAKES ONE PULL OF THE
STRING TO BRING THEM TO LIFE.

13:31.071 --> 13:32.507
BUT IF ALL THE PIECES AREN'T
PERFECTLY LINKED TOGETHER --

13:32.594 --> 13:35.205
Moz:
IT ALL COLLAPSES.

13:35.292 --> 13:38.643
I'VE...HEARD
THIS STORY BEFORE.

13:38.730 --> 13:40.776
PARADISE COMES AT A PRICE,
MR. MAINE.

13:40.863 --> 13:42.778
YOU PULL THE STRINGS.

13:42.865 --> 13:44.171
AND I KEEP EVERYTHING
TIED TOGETHER.

13:44.258 --> 13:46.173
PLEASE HAVE A SEAT.

13:46.260 --> 13:47.783
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

13:50.438 --> 13:53.833
25 GRAND -- WHAT ASSURANCES
DOES THIS GUARANTEE US?

13:53.920 --> 13:55.835
IT ASSURES YOU
THE LOCAL LAW ENFORCEMENT

13:55.922 --> 13:58.185
WON'T DIVULGE
YOUR PRESENCE HERE,

13:58.272 --> 13:59.969
NOR WILL THEY HASSLE YOU.

14:00.056 --> 14:01.797
IF YOU HAVE ANY DISPUTES,

14:01.884 --> 14:04.365
PROBLEMS, ISSUES,
BRING THEM TO ME.

14:04.452 --> 14:06.715
EXTRADITION OR NOT,
THIS MONEY GUARANTEES

14:06.802 --> 14:09.326
THAT WE STAY INVISIBLE
TO THE OUTSIDE WORLD.

14:09.413 --> 14:10.937
THAT'S RIGHT.

14:11.024 --> 14:14.114
I ONLY ASK THAT YOU RESPECT
THE SANCTITY OF THE ISLAND.

14:14.201 --> 14:16.159
AND IF I HAVE CONCERN,
I COME TO YOU.

14:16.246 --> 14:17.987
ANYTIME, DAY OR NIGHT.

14:18.074 --> 14:19.423
BUT I DOUBT
HE'LL HAVE ANY.

14:19.510 --> 14:20.598
BUT I DO.
PLEASE DON'T.

14:20.685 --> 14:22.383
THERE'S A BOY IN TOWN --
HECTOR.

14:22.470 --> 14:23.863
HE RUNS A FRUIT STAND.

14:23.950 --> 14:25.690
ONE OF YOUR MEN
HAS BEEN TAKING HIS PAPAYAS

14:25.777 --> 14:27.214
WITHOUT PAYING FOR THEM.

14:34.264 --> 14:37.789
FROM NOW ON,
BRODY WILL PAY FOR HIS PAPAYAS.

14:37.877 --> 14:39.008
AND THE ONES
HE'S ALREADY TAKEN?

14:40.662 --> 14:44.361
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:46.711 --> 14:49.801
I'LL SEE TO IT
THE BOY IS COMPENSATED.

14:49.889 --> 14:51.107
ALL RIGHT.

14:51.194 --> 14:53.501
THEN I THINK
WE WILL BE VERY HAPPY HERE.

14:55.285 --> 14:57.244
EXCELLENT.

14:57.331 --> 14:59.855
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

15:03.598 --> 15:05.165
Moz:
PAPAYAS? SERIOUSLY?

15:05.252 --> 15:06.688
IT'S ABOUT JUSTICE, MOZ.

15:06.775 --> 15:08.559
AND IF
A CERTAIN CAFé GIRL

15:08.646 --> 15:10.431
GETS WIND
OF YOUR LITTLE GOOD DEED?

15:10.518 --> 15:11.475
ADDED BONUS.

15:11.562 --> 15:12.824
JUST SO YOU KNOW,

15:12.912 --> 15:14.914
HECTOR MAKES A KILLING
OFF THAT FRUIT STAND.

15:15.001 --> 15:16.524
THINK ABOUT THATTHE NEXT TIME
YOU GIVE ME AN EMBOLISM.

15:16.611 --> 15:18.004
[ SAFE DOOR CLOSES ]

15:18.091 --> 15:21.921
GENTLEMEN...
IT'S BEEN A PLEASURE.

15:30.451 --> 15:31.713
[ HORN HONKS ]

15:40.069 --> 15:43.899
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

15:52.603 --> 15:55.998
PERFECT TIMING.
COLLINS IS IN THERE NOW.

15:56.085 --> 15:57.434
E. PARKER?

15:57.521 --> 16:00.698
FEMALE.
MID- TO LATE-50s.

16:00.785 --> 16:02.352
WHAT'D YOU BRING ME?
AH.

16:02.439 --> 16:03.484
[ CHUCKLES ]
DEVILED HAM.

16:03.571 --> 16:04.702
OH, NEAL HATED THIS.

16:04.789 --> 16:06.487
THAT'S BECAUSE
HE HAD A NOSE.

16:06.574 --> 16:08.054
WHAT?
NOTHING.

16:08.141 --> 16:09.751
MMM.

16:09.838 --> 16:12.319
OH, STAKEOUTS WITH NEAL
WERE THE WORST.

16:12.406 --> 16:14.408
HOW SO?
WELL, HE'D --

16:14.495 --> 16:16.845
HE'D ALWAYS WANT TO LISTEN
TO PUBLIC RADIO

16:16.932 --> 16:21.458
OR TALK ABOUT CHIAROSCURO
IN ROMAN IMPERIAL MANUSCRIPTS.

16:21.545 --> 16:22.982
YOU MISS HIM.

16:23.069 --> 16:24.722
YEAH. YEAH, RIGHT.

16:24.809 --> 16:29.031
ESPECIALLY THE WAY HE'D RUN OFF
AFTER I TOLD HIM NOT TO.

16:29.118 --> 16:30.859
OH, DROVE ME CRAZY.

16:30.946 --> 16:32.904
YOU KNOW,
IF IT MAKES YOU FEEL BETTER,

16:32.992 --> 16:34.819
I COULD COME UP
WITH AN EXCUSE

16:34.906 --> 16:37.648
TO GET OUT OF THE CAR AND GO
EAVESDROP ON COLLINS BY...

16:37.735 --> 16:40.477
I DON'T KNOW, ZIP-LINING
ACROSS THE DRAINAGE PIPE

16:40.564 --> 16:43.524
WITH GRAPPLING HOOKS MADE OUT
OF EXPENSIVE FORZIERI TIES.

16:43.611 --> 16:46.875
IT MIGHT MAKE ME
FEEL A LITTLE BETTER.

16:46.962 --> 16:49.182
YOU'RE THE BEST WIFE EVER.
YOU KNOW THAT.

16:49.269 --> 16:52.881
[ CHUCKLES ]
OOH, OOH.

16:52.968 --> 16:55.318
LOOK AT THAT. REJECTED.NO. I'VE GOT NOTHING
TO SAY TO YOU.

16:55.405 --> 16:56.754
MAN ON DECK.

16:56.841 --> 16:58.234
ACTUALLY,
I WASON DECK.

16:58.321 --> 16:59.931
NOW I'M UP TO BAT,
TECHNICALLY.

17:00.019 --> 17:01.542
AH. RIGHT.

17:01.629 --> 17:03.065
THE BEST WIFE EVER WOULD HAVE
KNOWN THAT, WOULDN'T SHE?

17:03.152 --> 17:04.806
SHE WOULD.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

17:04.893 --> 17:06.155
GOOD LUCK.

17:06.242 --> 17:08.114
THANKS.

17:12.074 --> 17:15.773
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

17:15.860 --> 17:17.819
[ DOOR OPENS ]

17:17.906 --> 17:20.735
MS. PARKER, MY NAME
IS PETER BURKE. I WAS --

17:20.822 --> 17:22.737
I KNOW WHO YOU ARE, AND I'VE
ALREADY TOLD YOUR PARTNER

17:22.824 --> 17:24.173
I'VE GOT NOTHING TO SAY.

17:24.260 --> 17:26.088
AGENT COLLINS AND I
AREN'T PARTNERS.

17:26.175 --> 17:27.568
I'M NEAL'S FRIEND.

17:27.655 --> 17:30.353
YOU NEED SOMETHING MORE ORIGINAL
THAN GOOD COP/BAD COP.

17:30.440 --> 17:33.182
I'VE PLAYED THAT GAME MYSELF,
AND YOU'RE NOT VERY GOOD AT IT.

17:33.269 --> 17:34.618
NO,
I'M TRYING TO HELP HIM.

17:34.705 --> 17:35.663
WERE YOU
TRYING TO HELP HIM

17:35.750 --> 17:37.230
WHEN YOU LOCKED HIM UP
THE FIRST TIME?

17:37.317 --> 17:39.275
I WAS, BUT THAT --

17:39.362 --> 17:42.322
THEN I'M PRETTY CONFIDENT
HE DOESN'T WANT YOUR HELP NOW.

17:42.409 --> 17:46.021
MS. PARKER, I DON'T THINK
YOU UNDERSTAND WHAT --
NO.

17:48.197 --> 17:49.198
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

17:59.208 --> 18:00.122
COME, MISSES!
THIS WAY!

18:00.209 --> 18:02.516
WHERE ARE WE GOING,
HECTOR?

18:02.603 --> 18:04.518
[ SIGHS ]

18:13.353 --> 18:15.006
SURPRISE.

18:15.094 --> 18:17.139
DON'T TELL ME THE GUY
WHO STEALS HECTOR'S PAPAYAS

18:17.226 --> 18:19.533
OFFERS YOU WINE
AND CHOCOLATE.

18:19.620 --> 18:23.102
OUT OF NOWHERE,
HE PAID HECTOR BACK TODAY.

18:23.189 --> 18:26.061
I WONDER IF YOU HAVE ANYTHING
TO DO WITH THAT.

18:26.148 --> 18:29.108
I'M FLATTERED
THAT YOU THINK I WOULD.

18:31.588 --> 18:33.895
COME ON.
I'LL SHOW YOU THE VIEW.

18:37.246 --> 18:38.943
HMM. RIGHT THIS WAY.

18:39.030 --> 18:41.772
HERE.

18:41.859 --> 18:44.775
[ GASPS ]

18:44.862 --> 18:46.777
WOW.

18:46.864 --> 18:49.171
HOW DID YOU DO THIS?

18:49.258 --> 18:51.086
PLASTER MOLDS
AND A LOT OF SAND.

18:51.173 --> 18:52.566
[ GASPS ]

18:52.653 --> 18:54.089
IT'S THE VIEW
FROM MY OLD BUILDING.

18:54.176 --> 18:57.571
THIS IS AMAZING.

19:04.621 --> 19:06.754
WHY?

19:06.841 --> 19:09.844
I'LL NEVER
BE AN OPEN BOOK,

19:09.931 --> 19:13.935
BUT NEW YORK
WAS A PRETTY BIG CHAPTER.

19:14.022 --> 19:16.111
ARE YOU GOING TO BE HONEST
ABOUT IT?

19:16.198 --> 19:18.809
YOU ASKED ME
FOR A MOMENT OF HONESTY.

19:18.896 --> 19:20.420
I'M GONNA GIVE YOU 20.

19:20.507 --> 19:21.856
20?

19:21.943 --> 19:23.553
20 QUESTIONS.

19:23.640 --> 19:25.076
SO GENEROUS OF YOU.

19:25.164 --> 19:28.384
WELL,
I'M A GENEROUS GUY.

19:28.471 --> 19:30.299
ASK ME ANYTHING YOU WANT
ABOUT MY LIFE THERE.

19:30.386 --> 19:31.431
ANYTHING?
ANYTHING.

19:31.518 --> 19:32.954
OKAY.

19:33.041 --> 19:34.782
HONESTY.

19:37.567 --> 19:38.612
DO YOU MISS IT?

19:38.699 --> 19:40.353
EVERY DAY.

19:40.440 --> 19:43.834
I LIVED THERE OFF AND ON
SINCE I WAS 18, SO...

19:43.921 --> 19:45.271
WHY DID YOU GO THERE?

19:45.358 --> 19:46.968
I HAD TO LEAVE THE PLACE
I WAS FROM.

19:47.055 --> 19:48.404
WHERE WAS THAT?

19:48.491 --> 19:50.363
ST. LOUIS, BUT THAT'S NOT
A NEW YORK QUESTION.

19:50.450 --> 19:52.669
TRICKY.
OKAY, THEN,
IT DOESN'T COUNT.

19:52.756 --> 19:54.367
ALL RIGHT.
[ CHUCKLES ] OKAY.

19:54.454 --> 19:58.153
UM...DID YOU KNOW ANYONE
WHEN YOU ARRIVED?

19:58.240 --> 20:00.938
NOT A SOUL.

20:01.025 --> 20:03.289
WHO WAS
YOUR FIRST FRIEND?

20:03.376 --> 20:05.247
BARRY.

20:05.334 --> 20:07.162
HE DOESN'T LOOK
LIKE A BARRY.

20:07.249 --> 20:09.208
[ LAUGHS ]

20:09.295 --> 20:11.732
DO I LOOK LIKE A JAMES?

20:11.819 --> 20:14.648
THAT'S WHY I CALL YOU
"NEW YORK."

20:14.735 --> 20:17.128
I CAN LIVE WITH THAT.

20:17.216 --> 20:18.521
HEY.
HEY.

20:18.608 --> 20:19.957
ARE YOU ALONE?
YEAH.

20:20.044 --> 20:21.524
WHAT'S GOING ON.

20:21.611 --> 20:25.006
WELL, I MADE A GRAPPLING HOOK
OUT OF FORZIERI TIES.

20:26.616 --> 20:29.489
IT'S...YOU.

20:29.576 --> 20:32.056
CALL ME ELLEN.

20:32.143 --> 20:35.451
FOR THE RECORD, YOUR WIFE DOES
A VERY GOOD "GOOD COP."

20:35.538 --> 20:39.238
YES, SHE DOES.

20:39.325 --> 20:41.370
ELLEN...

20:41.457 --> 20:44.068
WE NEED TO TALK
ABOUT NEAL.

20:44.155 --> 20:47.855
HE DOESN'T KNOW IT YET,
BUT HE NEEDS OUR HELP.

20:53.904 --> 20:55.558
Ellen: I'M CURIOUS.

20:55.645 --> 20:57.299
WHAT EXACTLY
DID NEAL TELL YOU ABOUT ME?

20:57.386 --> 21:00.041
NOTHING.
NOT EVEN A NAME.

21:00.128 --> 21:02.696
YOU WERE NEAL'S
FATHER'S PARTNER.

21:02.783 --> 21:05.220
YOU TALK THE TALK.
PARTNERS ARE LIKE FAMILY.

21:05.307 --> 21:07.396
THAT'S IT, ISN'T IT?

21:07.483 --> 21:09.746
AGENT BURKE,
I DON'T MEAN TO BE RUDE,

21:09.833 --> 21:12.009
BUT I'M IN WITSEC
FOR A GOOD REASON.

21:12.096 --> 21:14.403
I'M NOT SO SURE
THIS WAS A GOOD IDEA.

21:14.490 --> 21:15.709
I'M SORRY TO HAVE
WASTED YOUR TIME.

21:15.796 --> 21:18.059
I GAVE NEAL
THE SIGNAL TO RUN.

21:18.146 --> 21:20.104
THE DAY OF
HIS COMMUTATION HEARING,

21:20.191 --> 21:21.976
THE DAY HE WOULD HAVE
GONE FREE,

21:22.063 --> 21:23.456
AN AGENT WITH A GRUDGE

21:23.543 --> 21:25.806
DECIDED NEAL DIDN'T
DESERVE THAT FREEDOM,

21:25.893 --> 21:28.461
SO HE WAS GONNA BE
HAULED OFF FOR LIFE.

21:28.548 --> 21:30.332
PRISON...
AN ANKLET IN D.C. --

21:30.419 --> 21:33.683
SOMETHING THAT
HE DIDN'T DESERVE.

21:33.770 --> 21:37.470
SO I GAVE HIM
THE SIGNAL TO RUN.

21:37.557 --> 21:40.864
YOU SET HIM FREE?

21:40.951 --> 21:43.389
AND NOW HE'S OUT THERE
SOMEWHERE.

21:43.476 --> 21:45.956
AND THE OTHER AGENT
WHO CAME TO YOU --

21:46.043 --> 21:47.306
AGENT COLLINS?

21:47.393 --> 21:49.308
HE WON'T STOP...

21:49.395 --> 21:53.747
UNTIL HE BRINGS NEAL BACK --
ALIVE OR...

21:53.834 --> 21:56.358
OR OTHERWISE.

21:56.445 --> 21:59.970
ELLEN, IF ANYTHING
WERE TO HAPPEN TO HIM, I...

22:00.057 --> 22:04.105
I DON'T THINK
I COULD LIVE WITH IT.

22:08.022 --> 22:12.592
I SENT NEAL OUT
INTO THE WORLD ONCE.

22:12.679 --> 22:15.377
TOLD HIM A TRUTH
HE WASN'T READY TO HANDLE.

22:15.464 --> 22:19.381
SIX YEARS AGO, WHEN THE FEDS
WERE CLOSING IN ON HIM,

22:19.468 --> 22:21.905
NEAL AND I
EXCHANGED PAGERS.

22:21.992 --> 22:24.081
IN CASE SOMETHING HAPPENED,

22:24.168 --> 22:27.084
WE'D USE THEM
LIKE EMERGENCY FLARES.

22:27.171 --> 22:29.304
ELLEN,
YOU WON'T REGRET THIS.

22:29.391 --> 22:31.480
PROTECT OUR BOY.

22:35.397 --> 22:37.921
[ PAGER BUZZING ]

22:40.141 --> 22:42.796
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

22:46.495 --> 22:49.150
[ BUZZING CONTINUES ]

23:05.166 --> 23:07.386
[ BUZZING CONTINUES ]

23:17.308 --> 23:20.007
[ BUZZING CONTINUES ]

23:20.094 --> 23:22.052
[ BEEP ]

23:22.139 --> 23:24.881
[ THUNDER RUMBLING ]

23:27.667 --> 23:30.670
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]

23:32.628 --> 23:35.370
[ Ringing ]

23:39.896 --> 23:41.985
[ Click ]

23:42.072 --> 23:43.552
ELLEN?

23:43.639 --> 23:45.554
HI, NEAL.

23:45.641 --> 23:47.817
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:47.904 --> 23:49.906
GUESS THIS MAKES YOU
3 AND 0.

23:49.993 --> 23:52.779
2 AND 1.
HAVEN'T FOUND YOU YET.

23:52.866 --> 23:55.042
ELLEN GAVE YOU
THE PAGER NUMBER?
Yeah.

23:55.129 --> 23:56.826
YEAH,
SHE SENDS HER BEST.

23:56.913 --> 23:59.742
I'M SURE.
WHAT DO YOU KNOW?

23:59.829 --> 24:02.266
NEAL, THE D.O.J. HAS GOT SOMEONE
LOOKING FOR YOU.

24:02.353 --> 24:03.964
WELL, IF THEY DIDN'T,
I'D BE INSULTED.

24:04.051 --> 24:06.009
HE MEANS BUSINESS.

24:06.096 --> 24:08.229
"HE" MEANING "YOU"?
No.

24:08.316 --> 24:10.405
[ BELL TOLLING ]THEN I'M NOT WORRIED.

24:12.276 --> 24:14.322
HOW BAD DID I LEAVE THINGS
FOR YOU?

24:14.409 --> 24:17.194
EH, THE BUREAU
BEAT ME UP A LITTLE,

24:17.281 --> 24:18.892
BUT I'M HANDLING IT.

24:18.979 --> 24:20.023
And Elizabeth?

24:20.110 --> 24:22.069
SHE'S GOOD.

24:25.551 --> 24:29.642
THE AGENT WHO IS AFTER YOU,
HIS NAME IS COLLINS.

24:29.729 --> 24:32.601
HE'S WITH THE OFFICE
OF INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS.

24:32.688 --> 24:34.951
HE'S DANGEROUS.

24:35.038 --> 24:37.954
And he won't stop
until he finds you.

24:38.041 --> 24:39.739
I'M SAFE HERE.

24:39.826 --> 24:41.697
AND I'M HAPPY.

24:41.784 --> 24:43.438
We had a good run.

24:43.525 --> 24:44.874
IT'S NOT OVER.

24:44.961 --> 24:46.963
Yeah, it is.

24:47.050 --> 24:49.052
YOU'RE AN FBI AGENT.
I'M A CON MAN.

24:49.139 --> 24:50.924
THERE ARE ONLY A FEW WAYS
THIS COULD HAVE ENDED.

24:51.011 --> 24:53.796
THIS IS
ONE OF THE BEST.

24:53.883 --> 24:56.799
RIGHT.

24:56.886 --> 25:00.499
YOU UNDERSTAND
THIS HAS TO BE THE LAST TIME.

25:00.586 --> 25:03.153
NEW YORK AND I ARE DONE.

25:03.240 --> 25:05.416
I GET IT.

25:05.504 --> 25:07.941
PLEASE WATCH OUT
FOR COLLINS.

25:08.028 --> 25:10.944
I WILL.

25:11.031 --> 25:13.163
IT'S GOOD
TO HEAR YOUR VOICE.

25:13.250 --> 25:15.949
YEAH. YOU TOO.

25:16.036 --> 25:18.038
GOOD-BYE, PETER.

25:18.125 --> 25:19.953
GOOD-BYE, NEAL.

25:20.040 --> 25:22.738
[ BEEP ]

25:22.825 --> 25:24.174
[ CELL PHONE CLOSES ]

25:24.261 --> 25:25.611
[ BEEP ]

25:25.698 --> 25:26.742
[ CELL PHONE CLOSES ]

25:29.179 --> 25:32.095
[ THUNDER CRASHING ]

25:41.496 --> 25:43.672
THANKS FOR COMING.
ANY SIGN OF COLLINS?

25:43.759 --> 25:45.108
Jones:
NOT SINCE YESTERDAY.

25:45.195 --> 25:46.980
MY FRIEND IN QUANTICO
SLIPPED THE RECORDING

25:47.067 --> 25:49.025
TO THE DIGITAL EVIDENCE
EXPLOITATION UNIT.

25:49.112 --> 25:50.418
SHE ISOLATED THREE DISTINCT

25:50.505 --> 25:52.159
BACKGROUND ELEMENTS
OF NEAL'S CALL.

25:52.246 --> 25:53.334
LISTEN.

25:53.421 --> 25:54.770
[ BELL TOLLING]

25:54.857 --> 25:56.859
CHURCH BELLS.

25:56.946 --> 25:59.166
FOUR IN A ROW.
THERE'S MORE.

25:59.253 --> 26:00.646
[ WAVES CRASHING]

26:00.733 --> 26:02.691
OCEAN TIDES.
RHYTHMIC.

26:02.778 --> 26:04.998
THEY WERE AUDIBLE
DURING THE CALL.

26:05.085 --> 26:06.956
LISTEN TO THAT
FOURTH WAVE AGAIN.

26:07.043 --> 26:09.350
[ THUNDER RUMBLES]

26:09.437 --> 26:11.831
IT'S OFF RHYTHM.

26:11.918 --> 26:14.268
IT'S NOT A WAVE.
IT'S THUNDER.

26:14.355 --> 26:15.530
ALL RIGHT.

26:15.617 --> 26:18.098
WE'VE GOT CHURCH BELLS
AND A STORM.

26:18.185 --> 26:19.490
IT'S A START, RIGHT?

26:19.578 --> 26:22.842
ALL RIGHT.
I'LL MAKE THE COFFEE.

26:31.024 --> 26:32.112
BIENVENUE.

26:32.199 --> 26:34.462
BIENVENUE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:34.549 --> 26:37.770
I DID SOME PRECURSORY DIGGING
INTO THIS COLLINS.

26:37.857 --> 26:39.206
WHAT'D YOU FIND?

26:39.293 --> 26:41.556
WELL, THINK
DOG THE BOUNTY HUNTER,

26:41.643 --> 26:44.167
SANS THE BLEACHED MULLET
AND BEL ESPRIT.

26:44.254 --> 26:45.821
SEEMS HE'D RATHER BRING HOME
HIS CAPTURES

26:45.908 --> 26:47.040
IN BODY BAGS
THAN NOT AT ALL.

26:47.127 --> 26:48.302
THE CALL WAS UNTRACEABLE.

26:48.389 --> 26:49.956
THE BEEPER
AND THE BURNER PHONE

26:50.043 --> 26:52.045
ARE IN THE BOTTOM
OF THE ATLANTIC -- IT'S DONE.

26:52.132 --> 26:53.133
YOU SURE?

26:53.220 --> 26:54.525
YEAH, I'M SURE, MOZ.

26:54.613 --> 26:55.570
GOOD.

26:55.657 --> 26:58.834
OH. VITAMIN "C."

27:03.143 --> 27:04.623
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

27:07.843 --> 27:09.584
MORNING.

27:09.671 --> 27:11.673
HEY. YOU'RE UP.

27:11.760 --> 27:14.633
HEY.
HEY.

27:14.720 --> 27:16.504
CAN I GET YOU
SOME BREAKFAST?

27:16.591 --> 27:18.941
THANKS. I SHOULD GET OVER
TO THE CAFé.

27:19.028 --> 27:20.116
CAN I SEE YOU TONIGHT?

27:20.203 --> 27:22.075
I'D LIKE THAT VERY MUCH.

27:24.817 --> 27:26.296
SEE YOU, BARRY.

27:29.778 --> 27:31.650
Moz:
SETTING DOWN ROOTS.

27:31.737 --> 27:34.914
SPICY ONES AT THAT.
I SUPPORT THIS.

27:35.001 --> 27:37.307
A HARD BEGINNING
MAKETH A GOOD ENDING.

27:37.394 --> 27:39.962
I'LL HAVE HECTOR KEEP AN EYE OUT
FOR COLLINS,

27:40.049 --> 27:41.268
JUST TO BE SAFE.

27:41.355 --> 27:42.573
TO GOOD ENDINGS.

27:42.661 --> 27:44.401
YES. [ SIGHS ]

27:44.488 --> 27:46.316
GOOD ENDINGS.[ GLASSES CLINK ]

27:50.581 --> 27:53.367
Peter:
THE CALL CAME IN AT MIDNIGHT.

27:53.454 --> 27:55.369
THE BELLS
RANG FOUR TIMES.

27:55.456 --> 27:57.850
LET'S ASSUME IT WAS 4:00 P.M.
WHERE NEAL WAS.

27:57.937 --> 27:59.373
VANUATU --

27:59.460 --> 28:02.376
WAVES, CHURCHES,
NO EXTRADITION -- IT WORKS.

28:02.463 --> 28:03.943
AH, IT'S NO GOOD.

28:04.030 --> 28:05.988
THE ONLY STORM ACTIVITY
AT 4:00 P.M. IN UTC PLUS-11

28:06.075 --> 28:08.164
OCCURRED UP
NEAR VLADIVOSTOK, RUSSIA.

28:08.251 --> 28:11.951
YEAH, MOZZIE IS AFRAID OF BEARS.
LET'S TRY 4:00 A.M.

28:12.038 --> 28:13.300
A LITTLE EARLY
FOR CHURCH.

28:13.387 --> 28:14.780
NO, NOT NECESSARILY.

28:14.867 --> 28:16.303
I SERVED MY TOUR NEAR
A CHAMORRO VILLAGE IN GUAM.

28:16.390 --> 28:18.609
LOCAL CHAPEL
HAD A 4:00 A.M. SERVICE

28:18.697 --> 28:20.263
FOR THE FISHERMEN
WHO WENT OUT BEFORE DAWN.

28:20.350 --> 28:22.309
PUTS HIM IN UTC MINUS-1.

28:22.396 --> 28:24.441
CAPE VERDE ISLANDS.

28:24.528 --> 28:25.965
NO EXTRADITION.

28:26.052 --> 28:28.663
ISOLATED THUNDERSTORMS
THROUGHOUT THE ATLANTIC,

28:28.750 --> 28:30.839
BUT, I MEAN, THERE MUST BE
DOZENS OF TINY ISLANDS.

28:30.926 --> 28:32.623
DIANA,
WHAT ABOUT THE BELLS?

28:32.711 --> 28:34.582
WELL, ANALYSIS SAYS
THEY WERE SPANISH BRASS,

28:34.669 --> 28:37.106
BUT THE ISLANDS IN THAT
AREA WERE COLONIZED BY
PORTUGAL, NOT SPAIN.

28:37.193 --> 28:38.891
DEAD END.

28:38.978 --> 28:41.067
WE NEED SPANISH BELLS.

28:41.154 --> 28:42.546
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

28:42.633 --> 28:44.592
WAIT A SECOND.
I THINK I MAY HAVE SOMETHING.

28:44.679 --> 28:47.595
IN 1798, A BELL WAS DREDGED
FROM THE WRECKAGE

28:47.682 --> 28:50.163
OF A SPANISH SHIP
NAMED THE TRINIDAD.

28:50.250 --> 28:51.860
IT WAS HUNG IN THE CHURCH
OF ST. CHRISTOPHER

28:51.947 --> 28:53.296
IN THE PORT CITY OF SANTA MARIA

28:53.383 --> 28:56.212
ON THE NORTHERNMOST COAST
OF CAPE VERDE.

28:56.299 --> 28:59.302
AND YOU GOT TO LOVE
THE INTERNET,

28:59.389 --> 29:01.435
BECAUSE I HAVE A TOURIST VIDEO
WITH THE BELLS RINGING.

29:01.522 --> 29:03.219
[ BELLS TOLLING]

29:03.306 --> 29:04.960
DIANA?
ALREADY ON IT.

29:05.047 --> 29:06.875
[ TOLLING CONTINUES]

29:11.314 --> 29:13.142
YES!

29:13.229 --> 29:15.536
OH, YOU GOT TO LOVE THE SOUND
OF SPANISH BRASS!

29:15.623 --> 29:17.146
WE GOT HIM!

29:17.233 --> 29:18.887
WHAT NOW?GO BACK TO THE OFFICE

29:18.974 --> 29:20.367
AND FIGURE OUT A WAY
TO BRING NEAL HOME.

29:26.025 --> 29:29.289
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

29:29.376 --> 29:31.247
ELIZABETH BURKE.YES.

29:31.334 --> 29:32.553
AGENT COLLINS.

29:32.640 --> 29:35.034
UH, MY HUSBAND'S ACTUALLY
AT THE OFFICE.

29:35.121 --> 29:36.600
I KNOW.

29:36.687 --> 29:38.559
WELL, THEN,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?MY JOB.

29:38.646 --> 29:40.648
YOU CAN'T JUST WALK IN
LIKE THIS.

29:40.735 --> 29:43.564
DOES AGENT HUGHES
KNOW ABOUT THIS?HE WILL.

29:43.651 --> 29:45.131
I'M CALLING MY HUSBAND.

29:45.218 --> 29:47.263
SIR,
TAKE A LOOK AT THIS.

29:54.749 --> 29:57.926
NO NEED TO BOTHER YOUR HUSBAND,
MRS. BURKE.

29:58.013 --> 30:00.146
I FOUND
WHAT I WAS LOOKING FOR.

30:02.452 --> 30:05.499
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:10.765 --> 30:12.332
COLLINS WAS IN MY HOUSE.

30:12.419 --> 30:13.855
HE HAD ABSOLUTELY NO RIGHT
TO BE THERE.

30:13.942 --> 30:15.552
HE HAD EVERYRIGHT.

30:15.639 --> 30:17.598
YOU WERE WITHHOLDING INFORMATION
ON CAFFREY'S WHEREABOUTS.

30:17.685 --> 30:19.905
I WAS SPECULATING
ON MY FREE TIME.

30:19.992 --> 30:22.385
I SAW THE MAP.
YOU CIRCLED CAPE VERDE.

30:22.472 --> 30:23.778
IS HE THERE?

30:23.865 --> 30:25.824
I DON'T KNOW.

30:27.347 --> 30:29.958
[ SIGHS ]
I THINK SO.

30:31.264 --> 30:33.440
COLLINS?

30:33.527 --> 30:34.615
HE WAS ON THE FIRST FLIGHT
TO CAPE VERDE.

30:34.702 --> 30:36.008
DOES HE HAVE
JURISDICTION?
NO.

30:36.095 --> 30:39.011
THEN HOW DO YOU THINK
HE'S GONNA BRING NEAL BACK?

30:39.098 --> 30:41.491
CAFFREY'S FATE IS OUT
OF YOUR HANDS, PETER.

30:41.578 --> 30:42.841
I DON'T ACCEPT THAT.

30:42.928 --> 30:44.146
WELL, YOU BETTER.

30:44.233 --> 30:45.582
PENDING REVIEW
OF THE SITUATION,

30:45.669 --> 30:47.236
I'VE BEEN INSTRUCTED
TO PUT YOU ON LEAVE.

30:47.323 --> 30:48.847
DO YOURSELF A FAVOR.

30:48.934 --> 30:51.632
USE THIS TIME
TO GET SOME PERSPECTIVE.

30:51.719 --> 30:53.852
THINK ABOUT
WHAT'S IMPORTANT.

30:53.939 --> 30:57.246
IF YOU DECIDE
IT'S CAFFREY...

30:57.333 --> 31:00.989
I UNDERSTAND,
BUT I CAN'T PROTECT YOU.

31:01.076 --> 31:03.078
DO YOUUNDERSTAND?

31:04.993 --> 31:06.995
COMPLETELY.

31:12.392 --> 31:14.698
SEÑOR MAINE,
SEÑOR SOETORO!

31:14.785 --> 31:17.788
I THINK I SAW THAT MAN
AT THE AEROPUERTO!

31:17.876 --> 31:19.529
HE FIT THE DESCRIPTION?

31:19.616 --> 31:21.488
SOLO AMERICANO
IN A DIPLOMATIC LINE.

31:21.575 --> 31:22.532
HAD VERY SMALL LUGGAGE.

31:22.619 --> 31:24.491
TIENE SU LA FOTO?

31:24.578 --> 31:26.362
Sí, sí, sí.
I HAVE ONE.

31:28.408 --> 31:30.453
[ SIGHS ] THIS SURE
LOOKS LIKE HIS FILE PHOTO.

31:30.540 --> 31:32.107
HOW DID HE FIND US?

31:32.194 --> 31:34.022
PETER SAID HE WAS GOOD.

31:34.109 --> 31:35.371
GOOD WORK, HECTOR.THANK YOU.

31:35.458 --> 31:37.591
KEEP EYES.OKAY. I KEEP EYES.

31:37.678 --> 31:39.201
THANK YOU, HECTOR.DON'T WORRY.

31:39.288 --> 31:42.117
WE HAVE MAYBE 24 HOURS.
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO DO?

31:42.204 --> 31:47.035
WHAT CHOICE DO I HAVE?
THIS ISLAND'S BURNED.

31:55.565 --> 31:57.437
COLLINS IS MAKING HIS WAY
TO SANTA MARIA.

31:57.524 --> 32:00.179
WE'RE ON BORROWED
ISLAND TIME.

32:00.266 --> 32:03.269
SAY GOOD-BYE TO THE LAST TRACES
OF JAMES MAINE.

32:03.356 --> 32:04.748
[ SIGHS ]

32:04.835 --> 32:06.620
EVEN THOUGH THEY'RE FORGERIES,
THIS STILL HURTS.

32:10.145 --> 32:13.279
I REALLY THOUGHT I WAS DONE
RUNNING THIS TIME.

32:13.366 --> 32:16.195
WE SHOULD GET
TO THE AIRPORT.

32:16.282 --> 32:18.327
MOZ.

32:18.414 --> 32:21.113
COLLINS IS ONLY AFTER ME.
YOU DON'T HAVE TO GO.

32:21.200 --> 32:24.333
YOU RUN, I RUN.
THAT'S THE DEAL.

32:24.420 --> 32:26.770
THEN LET'S RUN.

32:30.078 --> 32:33.299
[ LATIN MUSIC PLAYS ]

32:41.002 --> 32:43.178
[ BRAKES SQUEAL ]

32:45.920 --> 32:47.878
[ HORN BLARES ]

32:47.966 --> 32:49.793
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

33:06.897 --> 33:08.464
PARDONA.

33:08.551 --> 33:11.250
COMO PUEDO LLEGAR
A SANTA CRISTOBAL?

33:11.337 --> 33:12.860
AH, Sí.
THE CHURCH?

33:12.947 --> 33:14.514
Sí, THE CHURCH.

33:14.601 --> 33:16.820
MUCHAS GRACIAS.

33:39.191 --> 33:40.235
HOLA.

33:40.322 --> 33:42.455
HEY.
BUENOS DíAS, SEÑOR.

33:42.542 --> 33:43.847
[ CHUCKLES ]

33:43.934 --> 33:46.024
ARE YOU LOOKING FOR
A PARTICULAR TYPE OF HAT?

33:46.111 --> 33:47.677
[ Chuckling ] OH, NO.

33:47.764 --> 33:50.506
ACTUALLY, I'M, UH --
I'M LOOKING FOR A FRIEND.

33:50.593 --> 33:52.856
OH! SEÑOR MAINE.

33:52.943 --> 33:54.771
YES, SEÑOR MAINE.
YES.

33:54.858 --> 33:57.992
SKINNY BRIM,
ABOUT 25 VUELTAS,

33:58.079 --> 33:59.167
CLASSIC RIBBON.

33:59.254 --> 34:01.517
AH, SEÑOR MAINE
LOVES THE CLASSICS.

34:01.604 --> 34:02.692
MM-HMM.

34:02.779 --> 34:03.737
DO YOU KNOW
WHERE I CAN FIND HIM?

34:03.824 --> 34:06.827
HE ALSO LOVES COFFEE.

34:06.914 --> 34:09.177
COME.

34:13.616 --> 34:15.401
YOU SEE?
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:15.488 --> 34:16.402
COFFEE.

34:16.489 --> 34:17.794
MM-HMM.

34:17.881 --> 34:18.882
HIS BIGGEST WEAKNESS.

34:18.969 --> 34:19.883
MM.

34:19.970 --> 34:21.407
GRACIAS.

34:21.494 --> 34:24.105
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU HAVE A GOOD DAY, SIR.

34:24.192 --> 34:26.107
[ RATTLING ]

34:26.194 --> 34:28.762
SO, WHAT BRINGS YOU
TO THE ISLAND?

34:28.849 --> 34:31.243
I'M LOOKING FOR A FRIEND.

34:31.330 --> 34:35.464
DARK HAIR, I THINK BLUE EYES.
HE'S ANNOYINGLY PERSUASIVE.

34:35.551 --> 34:37.379
MAYBE YOU'VE SEEN HIM.

34:39.164 --> 34:40.339
MM, NOPE.

34:40.426 --> 34:41.557
HMM.

34:44.865 --> 34:47.128
OH! SHH!
IT'S COLLINS!

34:47.215 --> 34:49.739
12:00.

34:52.829 --> 34:54.048
HAS HE DONE SOMETHING?

34:54.135 --> 34:56.920
NOT AT ALL.
I OWE HIM AN APOLOGY.

34:57.007 --> 34:59.532
IT'S A LONG WAY TO COME
TO SAY YOU'RE SORRY.

34:59.619 --> 35:03.101
HE'S A GOOD FRIEND.
HE'S WORTH IT.

35:03.188 --> 35:05.451
WELL, LOOKY HERE.
AGENT BURKE.

35:05.538 --> 35:07.148
NEVER MIND.
I'M SURE YOU HAVEN'T SEEN HIM.

35:07.235 --> 35:08.802
Collins: I WONDER.

35:08.889 --> 35:12.022
WHAT COULD YOU BE DOING SO FAR
FROM HOME ON A TINY ISLAND?

35:12.110 --> 35:14.677
I IMAGINE THE SAME THING
THAT BROUGHT YOU HERE.

35:14.764 --> 35:17.245
GETTING THE BEST ORANGE GROGUE
FOR THE PRICE.

35:17.332 --> 35:18.942
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU KNOW, IT TOOK ME A DAY

35:19.029 --> 35:20.422
TO FIND CAFFREY'S
ISLAND HANGOUT.

35:20.509 --> 35:22.642
WHAT'D IT TAKE YOU --
FIVE MINUTES?

35:22.729 --> 35:24.731
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

35:24.818 --> 35:26.559
THE SUIT'S HERE
WITH ISLAND SUIT.

35:26.646 --> 35:28.691
IT'S A DOUBLE-BARRELED
SUIT.

35:28.778 --> 35:29.997
THAT'S HOW COLLINS FOUND US.

35:30.084 --> 35:32.608
NO. NO. THEY'RE NOT WORKING
TOGETHER. THEY CAN'T BE.

35:32.695 --> 35:35.785
YOU'RE GOOD, BURKE.
I'LL GIVE YOU THAT.

35:35.872 --> 35:38.136
BUT I HAVEN'T PLAYED
MYTRUMP CARD.

35:38.223 --> 35:41.965
SEÑORS AND SEÑORAS!
YOUR ATTENTION, PLEASE.

35:42.052 --> 35:43.315
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING?

35:43.402 --> 35:46.100
YOU MAY KNOW THIS MAN
AS JAMES MAINE.

35:46.187 --> 35:48.537
HIS REAL NAME
IS NEAL CAFFREY.

35:48.624 --> 35:52.411
CON MAN, ART THIEF,
FORGER, FUGITIVE.

35:52.498 --> 35:54.152
VAMANOS.
WE HAVE TO GO NOW.

35:54.239 --> 35:56.763
IT WON'T WORK, MOZ.
THEY'RE NOT GONNA GIVE ME UP.

35:56.850 --> 36:00.636
I'M OFFERING $500,000 AMERICAN
FOR THE CAPTURE OF THIS MAN.

36:00.723 --> 36:03.770
YOU BRING HIM TO ME,
AND THE MONEY'S YOURS.

36:03.857 --> 36:05.815
UNLESS THEY'RE PAID TO.

36:18.437 --> 36:20.526
Collins:
TAKE A GOOD LOOK AT THAT.

36:20.613 --> 36:22.310
ALL RIGHT?

36:22.397 --> 36:24.486
NOW, TAKE A GOOD LOOK
AT HIS FACE.

36:24.573 --> 36:26.271
I DON'T CARE WHAT CONDITION
YOU BRING HIM TO ME.

36:26.358 --> 36:27.446
JUST BRING HIM TO ME.

36:27.533 --> 36:28.838
COLLINS,
WHAT'S THAT ABOUT?

36:28.925 --> 36:30.449
[ CHUCKLES ]
WE ALL HAVE OUR METHODS.

36:30.536 --> 36:31.711
WERE YOU ORDERED
TO BRING HIM BACK ALIVE

36:31.798 --> 36:33.060
OR JUST BRING HIM BACK?

36:33.147 --> 36:35.889
OH, I'M SORRY, DID I NOT
SPECIFY "ALIVE"? OH.

36:35.976 --> 36:37.412
GO AHEAD.
ARREST ME, AGENT.

36:37.499 --> 36:39.022
OH, THAT'S RIGHT.
YOU CAN'T.

36:39.109 --> 36:40.372
YOU HAVE NO
JURISDICTION HERE.

36:40.459 --> 36:41.764
NEITHER DO YOU.

36:41.851 --> 36:43.723
THAT'S WHY I NEED THE HELP
OF THESE GOOD PEOPLE.

36:43.810 --> 36:45.464
HEY!

36:45.551 --> 36:46.900
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:46.987 --> 36:47.901
THAT'S MY WALLET,
KID!

36:47.988 --> 36:49.163
HEY, IF YOU NEED CASH,

36:49.250 --> 36:51.121
I KNOW HOW YOU COULD MAKE
HALF A MILLION!

37:00.130 --> 37:03.177
[ GROANS ]

37:10.315 --> 37:12.708
NO, NO.

37:20.150 --> 37:22.892
[ SIGHS ]

37:22.979 --> 37:24.546
Neal: YOU KNOW,
I USED TO TAKE PRIDE

37:24.633 --> 37:26.940
IN BEING ABLE
TO STEAL YOUR WALLET.

37:27.027 --> 37:29.986
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

37:30.073 --> 37:33.251
BUT IF A KID
CAN DO IT...

37:42.869 --> 37:44.958
HOW ARE YOU, PETER?

37:45.045 --> 37:47.961
[ SIGHS ]
ALL RIGHT.

37:48.048 --> 37:49.267
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

37:53.271 --> 37:54.837
DAMN GOOD TO SEE YOU.

37:54.924 --> 37:57.057
YOU TOO.

37:59.277 --> 38:00.930
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

38:01.017 --> 38:02.192
LOOK, NEAL, I --

38:02.280 --> 38:04.325
Moz:
AWFULLY CONVENIENT, SUIT.

38:04.412 --> 38:06.545
NEAL CALLS YOU,
AND THE NEXT DAY

38:06.632 --> 38:09.112
YOU'RE SHARING PIÑA COLADAS
WITH THE SUPER-SUIT

38:09.199 --> 38:10.331
ON OUR ISLAND?

38:10.418 --> 38:11.724
IT WAS THE ONLY WAY
I COULD WARN YOU.

38:11.811 --> 38:13.682
COLLINS IS DANGEROUS.

38:13.769 --> 38:16.685
WE NOTICED. HE'S TURNED
HALF THE ISLAND AGAINST US.

38:16.772 --> 38:19.340
WHICH IS WHY WE NEED TO GET OUT
OF HERE AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

38:19.427 --> 38:20.863
ALL RIGHT.
THE AIRPORT'S BURNED.

38:20.950 --> 38:22.300
THEY'LL BE LOOKING
FOR US THERE.

38:22.387 --> 38:25.085
THEN BY SEA IT IS.

38:25.172 --> 38:27.043
MY ASSOCIATE LORENZO
HAS A CHARTER BOAT.

38:27.130 --> 38:28.567
CAN HIS SILENCE
BE BOUGHT?

38:28.654 --> 38:31.047
OH, PLEASE. I OFFICIATED
HIS DAUGHTER'S WEDDING.

38:31.134 --> 38:32.527
HE CAN DROP US OVER HERE.

38:32.614 --> 38:33.833
Neal: NITSAE ISLAND.

38:33.920 --> 38:35.617
WE CAN LAY LOW THERE
FOR A WEEK OR TWO.

38:35.704 --> 38:38.011
YEAH, THEN WHAT?I DO KNOW A PLACE --

38:38.098 --> 38:40.056
UPSIDE, BEAUTIFUL
BLACK SAND BEACHES.

38:40.143 --> 38:41.667
DOWNSIDE?
LEPERS.

38:41.754 --> 38:43.886
WELCOME TO PARADISE.ALL RIGHT, LISTEN.

38:43.973 --> 38:45.410
WORD IS SPREADING
WITH EVERY PASSING MINUTE.

38:45.497 --> 38:46.585
WE HAVE TO MOVE NOW.

38:46.672 --> 38:47.934
VAMANOS.

38:48.021 --> 38:49.805
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

38:52.460 --> 38:54.332
Neal: DID YOU --Peter: I DID.

38:54.419 --> 38:55.724
DIDN'T TAKE LONG.

38:55.811 --> 38:57.291
NO.

39:01.295 --> 39:03.341
[ GRUNTS ][ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

39:05.168 --> 39:06.561
NICE SHOT,
CASSIUS CLAY.

39:06.648 --> 39:08.737
IT'LL BE EASIER ON MY OWN.
I'LL MEET YOU AT THE WHARF.

39:08.824 --> 39:10.217
NO,
IT'S TOO DANGEROUS.

39:10.304 --> 39:11.827
WORST CASE, I'LL HIDE OUT
SOMEWHERE, MEET YOU BEFORE DAWN.

39:11.914 --> 39:13.394
NEAL,
THE SUIT ISN'T WRONG.

39:13.481 --> 39:14.482
CAN'T YOU JUST SAY
I'M RIGHT?

39:14.569 --> 39:15.701
RATHER NOT!

39:15.788 --> 39:17.572
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

39:19.792 --> 39:21.663
[ GROANS ]

39:28.670 --> 39:30.498
[ ENGINE REVS ]

39:57.873 --> 39:59.222
[ ENGINE SHUTS OFF ]

39:59.309 --> 40:01.224
ARE YOU SURE YOU'RE
GONNA BE SAFE HERE TONIGHT?

40:01.311 --> 40:02.791
YEAH, IF DOBBS
GIVES ME PROTECTION,

40:02.878 --> 40:04.619
I CAN HEAD TO THE DOCKS
AFTER SUNDOWN.

40:04.706 --> 40:06.752
LOOK, I KNOW I PROMISED YOU
I WOULDN'T BRING TROUBLE.

40:06.839 --> 40:09.450
THANK YOU FOR BEING
AN OPEN BOOK, NEW YORK.

40:09.537 --> 40:11.365
IT WAS A FUN READ.

40:11.452 --> 40:14.847
ACTUALLY, IT'S NEAL.
NEAL CAFFREY.

40:14.934 --> 40:17.763
BE SAFE, NEAL CAFFREY.

40:23.856 --> 40:25.423
GO.

40:30.819 --> 40:33.822
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYS ]

40:33.909 --> 40:37.913
JAMES, COME IN.
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

40:38.000 --> 40:40.350
YOU SAID TO COME TO YOU
ANYTIME, DAY OR NIGHT, RIGHT?

40:40.438 --> 40:42.483
I DID.

40:42.570 --> 40:44.659
HAVE A SEAT.
LET ME GET YOU A DRINK.

40:49.229 --> 40:51.100
WHAT'S GOING ON?

40:51.187 --> 40:54.669
I NEED AN ESCORT
OFF THE ISLAND.

40:54.756 --> 40:56.758
HMM.

40:56.845 --> 40:57.759
[ BOTTLE THUDS ]

40:57.846 --> 40:59.021
REALLY, LORENZO?

40:59.108 --> 41:01.763
WE ATE CONCH TOGETHER.
DOES THAT MEAN NOTHING?

41:01.850 --> 41:03.635
THAT'S MY PRICE FOR TRANSPORT,
SEÑOR SOETORO.

41:03.722 --> 41:05.071
TAKE IT OR LEAVE IT.

41:05.158 --> 41:06.942
FINE. TAKE.

41:07.029 --> 41:08.683
BUT THIS IS
HIGHWAY ROBBERY --

41:08.770 --> 41:11.425
BY SEA.
SEAWAY ROBBERY!

41:13.079 --> 41:15.124
THAT WENT WELL.

41:15.211 --> 41:17.170
WELL, WE HAVE OUR WAY
OFF THE ISLAND.

41:17.257 --> 41:20.216
NOW ALL WE NEED IS OUR
HALF-A-MILLION-DOLLAR MAN.

41:20.303 --> 41:22.567
I'M SURE
HE'S ON HIS WAY.

41:22.654 --> 41:25.831
OR THERE'S
THE WORST CASE.

41:25.918 --> 41:28.355
[ SIGHS ] RIGHT.

41:28.442 --> 41:31.837
THIS MAY BE A LONG NIGHT.

41:35.188 --> 41:36.711
IT'S ALMOST SUNDOWN.

41:36.798 --> 41:38.147
WITH YOUR MEN'S PROTECTION,
I THINK IT'S SAFE ENOUGH --

41:38.234 --> 41:41.281
TRANSPORT'S STILL EN ROUTE.
WHAT'S YOUR RUSH?

41:43.675 --> 41:45.938
THANK YOU AGAIN
FOR ALL YOUR HELP.

41:46.025 --> 41:48.331
IT'S WHAT YOU PAY ME FOR,
ISN'T IT?

41:48.418 --> 41:50.377
KEEP THE LOCAL GOVERNMENT
OUT OF YOUR HAIR.

